Nothing working to stop overeating? It‚Äôs not your fault. Here's why:‚†Ä
‚†Ä
Diets and mainstream methods to control eating - even the healthy balanced lifestyle approach ones - do some crazy stuff to your brain and body.‚†Ä‚†Ä
‚†Ä
In short, they activate a response inside of you (think of it kind of like a "switch" that gets flipped on) that literally makes you tunnel visioned to overeat. ‚†Ä‚†Ä
‚†Ä
This gets even more difficult in times of years like the holidays with all the sweet treats, parties, and so forth!‚†Ä
‚†Ä
If you ever experience more that 3 of the following, then it's a tell-tale sign that this "overeating switch" is flipped on for you‚Ä¶‚†Ä‚†Ä
‚†Ä
‚ùå‚ÄãYou think about food a ton ‚†Ä‚†Ä
‚†Ä
‚ùåYou're cravings or urges to overeat are really hard to say no to‚†Ä‚†Ä
‚†Ä
‚ùåOnce you start with "forbidden" foods you tend to finish what's on your plate or in the bag‚†Ä‚†Ä
‚†Ä
‚Äã‚ùåYou don't feel "satisfied" often but rather need to eat a lot to feel full‚†Ä‚†Ä
‚†Ä
‚Äã‚ùåYou don't know when to stop with your eating and how much food is enough to take care of your body ‚†Ä‚†Ä
‚†Ä
‚ùåFood isn't easy. You have to work hard to control yourself‚†Ä‚†Ä
‚†Ä
UGH, I was there for years - no fun!‚†Ä‚†Ä
‚†Ä
And here's the catch...‚†Ä‚†Ä
‚†Ä
When your brain and body are in this place, NOTHING works! ‚†Ä‚†Ä
‚†Ä
The strongest will power, best coach, ninja trick, or most incredible plan in the world will not override your physiology! ‚†Ä‚†Ä
‚†Ä
So, you have to do something different...‚†Ä‚†Ä
‚†Ä
And that‚Äôs why we are SO EXCITED about bringing back our Challenge to "Overcome Overeating"!‚†Ä

In the challenge, I'll show you a different path that actually WORKS with your brain and body instead of against it! AKA we'll flip the switch off in your brain that makes you think about food a ton, have cravings, and overeat.‚†Ä

REMINDER as we go into th.e weekend... You always have a choice,
.
and you get to choose love even when it‚Äôs hard. .
By love I mean truth, .
.
And choosing the opposite of fear based decisions and perspective. .
.
Love when it's easy,
.
and love when it's hard.
.
Love when EVERYTHING says go all in, .

and love when EVERYTHING is telling you not to.
.

and love when you have no idea what you're going to do.

I know that it's hard when you're struggling with something to imagine being kind, loving, and compassionate to yourself...
